eu.amidst.core.utils

Class FixedBatchParallelSpliteratorWrapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.amidst.core.utils.FixedBatchParallelSpliteratorWrapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the elements of the underlying transversed stream.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Spliterator<T>

    public class FixedBatchParallelSpliteratorWrapper<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Spliterator<T>
    This class implements the Spliterator interface for providing streams which can be transversed using a batches of a fixed size. It is mainly used by the DataStream class to generate streams of batches of data instances, which are quite suitable for parallelizing data processing algorithms.

    For further details about the implementation of this class using Java 8 functional-style programming look at the following paper: Masegosa et al. Probabilistic Graphical Models on Multi-Core CPUs using Java 8. IEEE-CIM (2015).
